                        </MudListItem>
                        <MudListItem>
                            <MudIcon Icon="@Icons.Material.Filled.Extension" Size="Size.Medium" Class="align-sub"/>
                            Clean UI components such as image drag‑and‑drop uploads, icon selectors, and tool windows.
                        </MudListItem>
                        <MudListItem>
                            <MudIcon Icon="@Icons.Material.Filled.Sync" Size="Size.Medium" Class="align-sub"/>
                            Asynchronous data handling and custom utilities for database queries.
                        </MudListItem>
                        <MudListItem>
                            <MudIcon Icon="@Icons.Material.Filled.Brightness6" Size="Size.Medium" Class="align-sub"/>
                            Configurable dark/light themes with custom palettes and responsive layouts. (Still in progress)
                        </MudListItem>
                    </MudList>
                    <br/>
                    This project serves as a portfolio example to showcase practical development skills—database integration, dependency injection, and cloud-ready Blazor architecture. It demonstrates the same patterns used in production ERP systems but in a streamlined format designed for demo purposes. Potential clients and employers can explore this repository to see how I structure projects, style user interfaces, and manage data access using the latest .NET tools.
                    
                    The application is developed using <b>Blazor</b> and styled with <b>MudBlazor</b>, hosted on Azure, and backed by an SQL database — all configured with GitHub Actions for continuous deployment.
                    <br/>
                    <MudLink Href="https://github.com/bluke90/BlazorERP" Target="_blank" Class="link-git" Style="display: inline-block; margin-left: 0.5rem; margin-top: 0.5rem;">
                        BlazorERP Repo
